SensitiveFail
/ Fails an assertion where %MyIdentity% (which carries a [Sensitive] PrivateKey)
/ is the Actual value. Drives Identity into both AssertionError.Actual and the
/ captured Variables snapshot — the outer test verifies test.report masks the
/ PrivateKey as '******' before writing. %MyIdentity% is a reserved DynamicData
/ that lazily get-or-creates the default identity, so the fixture is idempotent
/ across runs (no "already exists" error).
- assert %MyIdentity% equals 'will-not-match'
